Overview

For this project, we expect to complete a user interface and database for the StoryAnalyzer application, complete with smooth controls for ease of access, a strong and in-depth security system, and a network across which users can share their individual analyses.

Major Project Goals

Our three major project goals are to provide an aesthetically-pleasing and easy-to-use interface, a strong user login with user creation and hashed passwords, and a functional and reliable connection between the website, database, and application.

Obstacles / Potential Technical Issues

Of the potential obstacles we could face on this project, we expect the most significant to be developing the connections between our website and the AWS databases, developing a user-friendly design that the client approves of, and difficulty with UI development due to a lack of a clear target audience.

Audience 

We expect our audience for this website to be journalists, historians, academics, and anyone else who needs to be able to understand a large text in a short period of time.

Timeline 

  • October 19th, 2021 - Sprint 1 Deliverables

Functioning rough draft that connects to the AWS database and the StoryAnalyzer to work with the Web App. Working User login with hashed passwords.
